# Linting & Formatting

After editing Python files, verify with the project toolchain:

```bash
export PYTHONPATH=src

# Format check
poetry run black --check src/ tests/

# Lint
poetry run flake8 src/ tests/

# Type check
poetry run mypy src/
```

Or use the Makefile shortcuts:

```bash
make format    # black src/ tests/
make lint      # flake8 src/ tests/
make typecheck # mypy src/
```

## Key rules (`.flake8`)
- `max-line-length = 100`
- `extend-ignore = E203, W503` (Black compatibility)

## Key rules (`pyproject.toml → [tool.mypy]`)
- `strict = true`
- `disallow_untyped_defs = true`
- `warn_return_any = true`

Fix all reported issues before committing. Never use `# type: ignore` without a comment explaining why.
